Play EuroMillions online

The European EuroMillions lottery was launched in 2004 and the first EuroMillions draw held on Friday the 13th of February in Paris. Initially, Spain, France and the UK were the only participating countries however, they were joined later that year by a further six countries; Austria, Belgium, Ireland, Luxembourg, Portugal and Switzerland. Now being drawn every Tuesday and Friday evenings, there are 13 different ways to win the Europe EuroMillions and a Jackpot cap of €190 million which makes it even more popular worldwide!

About EuroMillions

WIN THE EUROMILLIONS

Choose your five numbers from the guess range of 1 to 50 and the two additional numbers (EuroMillions lottery calls them Lucky Stars),which you have to select from a second matrix of 1 to 11 numbers and wish for the rising EuroMillions jackpot! The two Bonus numbers will appear highlighted after being chosen. If your chosen seven numbers match all the drawn winner figures, you will be the lucky owner of a first prize ticket! If your chosen numbers match only some of the EuroMillions set, you may also count on the two Bonus Numbers to allow you bite at secondary prizes.

LARGEST JACKPOT WON

The first EuroMillions winner was a 45-year-old mother of six from Ireland. She won £77 Million in July 2005. The largest jackpot in EuroMillions history was won and collected by Colin and Chris Weir from Lars, North Ayrshire on the August 12th 2011. Comprising not only the UK but, Europe’s biggest winners, their staggering windfall corresponded to a whopping €185,000,000! The biggest EuroMillions Jackpot win belongs to a participant from Portugal who won the lottery’s cap on October 24th 2014 of €190 Million!

Play EuroJackpot online

First launched in 2012 The Europe EuroJackpot has grown since rapidly and now available in Germany, Denmark, Finland, Sweden, Norway, Iceland, The Netherlands, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Slovenia, Croatia, Spain and also Italy, The pan European EuroJackpot is increasingly popular. With a guaranteed minimum jackpot every Friday of €10,000,000 the game is set to be a major competitor to the EuroMillions. The top prize will roll-over until it is won or until it hits the set cap of €90 million!

About EuroJackpot

WINNINGTHE EUROJACKPOT

In order for you to win the EuroJackpot, you will need to match all 7 numbers which consist of 5 main numbers you chose from a field of 1-5 and two lucky “Euro Numbers” that are selected from a field of 1-8. The goal of the game is to match your numbers with the numbers drawn. By matching a minimum of 2 numbers, you can win the smallest cash prizes. The more numbers you match the higher your prize will be. Match all 7 numbers and you win the jackpot prize. Prizes are shared equally among holders of lottery tickets.

LARGEST JACKPOTS WON

The biggest Jackpot for the EuroJackpot was set on September 13th, 2014 where a Lucky winner from Espoo, Finland won the €61,170,752.70 Jackpot! In January of 2013, another Finnish player from Seinäjoki was the happy winner of the €29,540,642 Jackpot, making it the biggest EuroJackpot prize won up to that time. A few months later, yet another Finn won more than €21 million in October of 2013. In April of 2014- 10 lucky winners from Finland as well, won €57.3 million in the EuroJackpot lottery!

Launched in 1997 by a private corporation, the SuperEnaLotto is a modification of EnaLotto in the 1950s. Since July 1, 2009 the numbers have been drawn independently. There is one single draw for the six numbers and the "Jolly" number and a second independent draw for the "SuperStar" number.

About SuperEnalotto

WINNING THE SUPERENALOTTO

The idea of this lotto is to match a combination of six numbers chosen from a number field of 1 to 90. Once your number combination matches the numbers drawn, you win the jackpot! If only three numbers match, you win any of the five categories The Jolly Number is like a bonus game that when you match it, you will win the 5 + 1 prize. But its effect is limited to second prizes, not its jackpot. Its primary purpose is to enable players to win a generous consolation prize if the jackpot is not hit. The superstar is another number with extra costs which offers prize multiplying option.

LARGEST JACKPOTS WON

In 2009 SuperEnaLotto had gone through continuous rollovers of jackpot prize extending over 8 months. After months of having no winner, the jackpot prize amounting to €147.8 million was claimed by a man hailing from Toscana, Italy. The highest jackpot prize ever recorded—€177.8 million was claimed after about nine months of rolling over in 2010.

The New York Lottery begins with a Jackpot of $2,000,000 and a guess range of 6 out of 59 numbers. New York Lottery is drawn twice a week on Wednesday and Saturday nights!

About NewYorkLotto

WINNING THE NEW YORK LOTTO

In order to win the jackpot, your selected main numbers must match all of the 6 main numbers drawn. The Bonus Number is the seventh number drawn and is used only for determining the 2nd prize level. A bonus number is selected automatically at the time of the ticket purchase. If you matched 5 out of the 6 main numbers but one of your selected numbers matches the 7th number drawn (the Bonus), you can win the 2nd prize. The Bonus number only affects the second prize and is not used for the lower prize level payouts. There are four secondary prize categories available to any player that matches three, four or five of the numbers drawn.

LARGEST JACKPOTS WON

The highest amount ever won in the New York Lotto was $65,000,000! This was won in June 2007. The starting Lotto jackpot was reduced from initially set sum of $3 million to $2 million in April 2013, rollovers were reduced from $500,000 to $300,000 over Thanksgiving weekend in 2012; in the late 1990s and its jackpot was $10 million after only one rollover!

Play ElGordo online

In Spanish, El Gordo translates to “the fat one”. Being one of the oldest and biggest lotteries in the world, the El Gordo began in 1763 by the Marquis of Esquilache. The old format allowed people to choose a combination of five numbers from 1 to 90. This lottery, one of the oldest in the world, was discontinued in 1862, but revived in 1985 with the introduction of the Loteria Nacional. The new format offered people a five-number combination from numbers 1 to 54 and the Reintegro number from 0 to 9. The El Gordo is drawn once a week on Sundays at 21:30 Local time. Offering Cash prizes to its lucky winners on a weekly base since it is well known for being won regularly.

About ElGordo

WINNING THE El GORDO

In order to win the El Gordo, you must guess correctly 5 numbers ranging (from 1 to 54) plus an additional number (from 0 to 9). This additional number will be the same for all bets on your ticket. Players have a 1:299 chance to match three numbers, a 1:14,342 chance of matching four, a 1:3,513,900 chance of matching five, and a 1:31,625,100 chance of matching 5+1.

LARGEST JACKPOTS WON

El Gordo kicks off with a starting Jackpot of €5 million and frequently rolls over. The highest El Gordo’s Jackpot to date was the €33,024,545 prize pool of 2011! In El Gordo de la Primitiva, the jackpot is rolled over to the next draw if results do not yield a first prize winner. That means if you did not win in a draw, you get a bigger prize if you win the next one! El Gordo de La Primitiva prizes are paid as a lump sum.
